:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=59&verse=4'>Isa 59:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=59&verse=13'>Isa 59:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=63&verse=8'>Isa 63:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=7&verse=8'>Jer 7:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=7&verse=28'>Jer 7:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=9&verse=3'>Jer 9:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=9&verse=6'>Jer 9:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=9&verse=8'>Jer 9:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=12&verse=6'>Jer 12:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=50&verse=36'>Jer 50:36</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=22&verse=9'>Eze 22:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=4&verse=2'>Hos 4:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=31&chapter=1&verse=7'>Oba 1:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=33&chapter=6&verse=12'>Mic 6:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=34&chapter=3&verse=1'>Nah 3:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=36&chapter=3&verse=13'>Zep 3:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=25&verse=46'>Mat 25:46</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=8&verse=45'>Joh 8:45</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=49&chapter=4&verse=25'>Eph 4:25</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=49&chapter=4&verse=29'>Eph 4:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=51&chapter=3&verse=9'>Col 3:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=54&chapter=1&verse=10'>1Ti 1:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=54&chapter=4&verse=2'>1Ti 4:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=60&chapter=3&verse=16'>1Pe 3:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=66&chapter=21&verse=8'>Rev 21:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=66&chapter=21&verse=27'>Rev 21:27</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=66&chapter=22&verse=15'>Rev 22:15</a><br/><a href='S:Accusation, False'>Accusation, False</a>; <a href='S:Conspiracy'>Conspiracy</a>; <a href='S:Deceit'>Deceit</a>; <a href='S:Deception'>Deception</a>; <a href='S:False Witness'>False Witness</a>; <a href='S:Flattery'>Flattery</a>; <a href='S:Hypocrisy'>Hypocrisy</a>; <a href='S:Perjury'>Perjury</a>; <a href='S:Teachers, False'>Teachers, False</a><br/> Instances of:<br/> - Satan:<br/> b in deceiving Eve<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=3&verse=5'>Gen 3:5</a><br/> b in impugning Job's motives for being righteous<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=18&chapter=1&verse=10'>Job 1:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=18&chapter=2&verse=5'>Job 2:5</a><br/> b in his false pretensions to Jesus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=4&verse=9'>Mat 4:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=4&verse=7'>Luk 4:7</a><br/> - Adam and Eve, in attempting to evade responsibility<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=3&verse=13'>Gen 3:13</a> <br/> - Cain, in denying knowledge of his brother<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=4&verse=9'>Gen 4:9</a> <br/> - Abraham, in denying that Sarah was his wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=12&verse=19'>Gen 12:19</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=20&verse=2'>Gen 20:2</a> <br/> - Sarah:<br/> b to the angels, denying her derisive laugh of unbelief<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=18&verse=15'>Gen 18:15</a><br/> b in denying to the king of Gerar, that she was Abraham's wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=20&verse=5'>Gen 20:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=20&verse=16'>Gen 20:16</a><br/> - Isaac, denying that Rebekah was his wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=26&verse=10'>Gen 26:10</a> <br/> - Rebekah and Isaac, in the conspiracy against Esau<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=27&verse=24'>Gen 27:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=27&verse=46'>Gen 27:46</a> <br/> - Jacob's sons, in the scheme to destroy the Shechemites by first having them circumcised<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=34'>Gen 34</a> <br/> - Joseph's brethren, in deceiving their father into a belief that Joseph was killed by wild beasts<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=37&verse=35'>Gen 37:35</a> <br/> - Potiphar's wife, in falsely accusing Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=39&verse=17'>Gen 39:17</a> <br/> - Joseph, in the deception he carried on with his brethren<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=42'>Gen 42</a> <br/> - Pharaoh, in dealing deceitfully with the Israelites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=7'>Exo 7</a> <br/> - Aaron, in attempting to shift responsibility for the making of the golden calf<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=32&verse=24'>Exo 32:24</a> <br/> - Rahab, in denying that the spies were in her house<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=2&verse=6'>Jos 2:6</a> <br/> - The Gibeonites, ambassadors, in the deception they perpetrated upon Joshua and the elders of Israel in leading them to believe that they came from a distant region, when in fact they dwelt in the immediate vicinity<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=9'>Jos 9</a> <br/> - Ehud, in pretending to bear secret messages to Eglon, king of Moab, while his object was to assassinate him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=3&verse=23'>Jdg 3:23</a> <br/> - Sisera, who instructed Jael to mislead his pursuers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=4&verse=20'>Jdg 4:20</a> <br/> - Saul:<br/> b in professing to Samuel to have obeyed the commandment to destroy all spoils of the Amalekites, when in fact he had not obeyed<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=15&verse=26'>1Sa 15:26</a><br/> b in accusing Ahimelech of conspiring with David against himself<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=22&verse=16'>1Sa 22:16</a><br/> - David:<br/> b Lied to Ahimelech, professing to have a mission from the king, in order that he might obtain provisions and armor<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=21&verse=15'>1Sa 21:15</a><br/> b in feigning madness<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=21&verse=15'>1Sa 21:15</a><br/> b Other deceits with the Philistines<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=12'>1Sa 27:12</a><br/> b the falsehood he put in the mouth of Hushai, of friendship to Absalom<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=15&verse=37'>2Sa 15:37</a><br/> - Michal, in the false statement that David was sick, in order to save him from Saul's violence<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19&verse=17'>1Sa 19:17</a> <br/> - The Amalekite who claimed to have slain Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=1&verse=12'>2Sa 1:12</a> <br/> - Hushai:<br/> b in false professions to Absalom<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=16&verse=19'>2Sa 16:19</a><br/> b in his deceitful counsel to Absalom<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=17&verse=14'>2Sa 17:14</a><br/> - The wife of the Bahurimite who saved the lives of Hushai's messengers, sent to apprise David of the movements of Absalom's army<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=17&verse=22'>2Sa 17:22</a> <br/> - The murder, under false pretense:<br/> b of Adonijah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=2&verse=23'>1Ki 2:23</a><br/> b of Shimei<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=2&verse=43'>1Ki 2:43</a><br/> b of Jeroboam's wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=14&verse=2'>1Ki 14:2</a><br/> - The old prophet of Beth-El who misguided the prophet of Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=13&verse=22'>1Ki 13:22</a> <br/> - Jeroboam's wife, feigning herself another woman<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=14&verse=7'>1Ki 14:7</a> <br/> - The conspirators against Naboth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=21&verse=13'>1Ki 21:13</a> <br/> - Gehazi, when he ran after Naaman, and misrepresented that Elisha wanted a talent of silver and two changes of raiment<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=5&verse=24'>2Ki 5:24</a> <br/> - Hazael, servant of the king of Syria, lied to the king in misstating the prophet Elisha's message in regard to the king's recovery<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=8&verse=15'>2Ki 8:15</a> <br/> - Jehu lied to the worshipers of Baal in order to gain advantage over them, and destroy them<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=10&verse=28'>2Ki 10:28</a> <br/> - Zedekiah, in violating his oath of allegiance to Nebuchadnezzer<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=36&verse=13'>2Ch 36:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=16&verse=59'>Eze 16:59</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=17&verse=20'>Eze 17:20</a> <br/> - Samaritans, in their efforts to hinder the rebuilding of the temple at Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=4'>Ezr 4</a> <br/> - Sanballat, in trying to obstruct the rebuilding of Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=6'>Neh 6</a> <br/> - Haman, in his conspiracy against the Jews<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=17&chapter=3&verse=8'>Est 3:8</a> <br/> - Jeremiah's adversaries, in accusing him of joining the Chaldeans<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=37&verse=15'>Jer 37:15</a> <br/> - Princes of Israel, when they went to Jeremiah for a vision from the Lord<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=42&verse=20'>Jer 42:20</a> <br/> - Herod, to the wise men, in professing to desire to worship Jesus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=2&verse=8'>Mat 2:8</a> <br/> - Jews:<br/> b in falsely accusing Jesus of being gluttonous and a winebibber<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=11&verse=19'>Mat 11:19</a><br/> b in refusing to bear truthful testimony concerning John the Baptist<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=21&verse=27'>Mat 21:27</a><br/> b Falsely accusing Jesus of blasphemy, when he remitted sin<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=9&verse=6'>Mat 9:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=2&verse=7'>Mar 2:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=5&verse=21'>Luk 5:21</a><br/> b Falsely accusing Jesus of blasphemy, when he announced that he was the Son of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=26&verse=65'>Mat 26:65</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=14&verse=64'>Mar 14:64</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=10&verse=38'>Joh 10:38</a><br/> - Peter, in denying Jesus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=26&verse=75'>Mat 26:75</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=14&verse=71'>Mar 14:71</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=22&verse=62'>Luk 22:62</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=18&verse=27'>Joh 18:27</a> <br/> - The Roman soldiers, who said the disciples stole the body of Jesus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=28&verse=13'>Mat 28:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=28&verse=15'>Mat 28:15</a> <br/> - The disobedient son, who promised to work in the vineyard, but did not<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=21&verse=30'>Mat 21:30</a> <br/> - Ananias and Sapphira falsely state that they had sold their land for a given sum<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=5&verse=10'>Act 5:10</a> <br/> - Stephen's accusers, who falsely accused him of blaspheming Moses and God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=6&verse=14'>Act 6:14</a> <br/> - Paul's traducers, falsely accusing him of treason to Caesar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=16&verse=21'>Act 16:21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=17&verse=7'>Act 17:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=24&verse=5'>Act 24:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=25&verse=8'>Act 25:8</a> <br/> - The Cretians are always liars, evil beasts, slow bellies<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=56&chapter=1&verse=12'>Tit 1:12</a><br/><a href='S:Accusation, False'>Accusation, False</a>; <a href='S:Conspiracy'>Conspiracy</a>; <a href='S:False Witness'>False Witness</a>; <a href='S:Hypocrisy'>Hypocrisy</a>; <a href='S:Perjury'>Perjury</a>; <a href='S:Teachers, False'>Teachers, False</a> "}]}